==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
According to oracle scripts and bronze inscriptions, a {{Han compound|止|王|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=foot|nocap=1}}. This is the original form of {{zh-m|*往}}.

According to small seal scripts, a {{Han compound|屮|王|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=sprout|nocap=1}}. Xu Shen misinterpreted it as a compound of {{zh-m|*𡳿/㞢|to go}} (now {{zh-m|*之}}) + {{zh-m|*土|earth, soil}}, influenced by {{zh-m|*封}}.

See also similar but unrelated {{zh-m|*𡴀}} (now {{zh-m|*丰}}) and {{zh-m|*𤯓}} (now {{zh-m|*生}}).

